caption: Amazing food, cute decor!
Best fine dining in Hayward. Eat here a few times a year. Always good.

Casual elegance that made for a great evening. Chopped salad, wild mushroom bruschetta, scallops, filet, chocolate cake and apropos wine list. Waiter added just the right touch of personality. Great for special night as well. Truly enjoyed. I highly recommended this place.

We had heard about this restaurant for a number of years but never made a reservation. Some friends invited us to meet them there. We had not even known the exact location until we arrived. It turns out to be in a beautiful old building across from city hall. The room was beautiful, the service was great.

I love Neumanali. The scallops and the fillet mignon are my favorite main dish. The ambient is amazing for a romantic night out with the wife, or to have a beer at the bar after a long meeting. Expect a great wine list, and be ready to appreciate the great art that decorates the place. Definitely the hidden jewel of the bay.

“Tip, top, the best” Wonderful: ambiance, food & service. Behind the scenes. This used to be Rue Du Main, French. The muralist was flown to France to sketch what became the street scenes surrounding the upper dining room. Roll forward …

Acqua & Farina is our go to place for great Italian dishes and upscale dining experience - in Hayward. We have eaten here a number of times and we fell in love with this restaurant from the very first. It is good for dinner for two or for couples.

“Amazing Dinner” Acqua E' Farina is in the Green Shutter building where Rue d' Main used to be - in downtown Hayward. The food is authentic and the quality is fantastic. They offer a broad menu along with daily specials. Great appetizers, too. My wife had chicken pesto pasta, and I had the special - Seafood pasta

“Have eaten here for decades!” Amazing food, sized to suit, Mama, Papa & Baby burgers cooked so you can watch. Service is excellent place is always packed, don't linger, we all want to get in ! I think the prices are very fair. It is not foo-foo food, it is real quality food.
Good size food selection with full bar and micro-brews... to be honest the beer on the guest taps are better than their house taps.

If you like hamburgers, this is fine place, Old School, right out of the 50's. Decent prices, no short cuts, real milkshakes, real French Fries, onion rings. The only think is that the burgers are cooked on a flattop, not a grill but that apart, a worthy destination.
Been eating these dogs since I was 6years old. Lots of imitations but only one original. If I had to choose my last meal, this would be it. The best was Harry's in Oakland.

A very nice and attractive restaurant. The two dinner dishes we ordered to go (first timer here) were pretty good - shrimp/chicken jambalaya (pretty good) and Mongolian beef (a bit on the salty side) came with nice portion plus brown rice. The price is reasonable.

Very nice place to eat in, the food is also good so you won't be disapointed in coming here. We loved the dfferent varriations of mexican food. The barbacoa is so yummy and we loved it. You also have burritos and chichimangas but you certainly would like to try the goat birria which is amazing and very tasty. Never had...
